Upcoming online workshop! 
-
I'm so excited to be included in @gasworksnyc's Women + GNC 9 online workshop series! 

Sundays, Jan 15-Mar 19, 2-4pm EST

This series of workshops will bring together the talents and perspectives of 10 women and gender non-conforming artists working in clay from around the country. Each week a different instructor will do an artist talk followed by a demonstration of one of their special skills or favorite techniques online via zoom. All classes will be recorded if you miss a class and you have access to the recordings for at least one year. We are now offering three price points: zoom only for $295, or take classes, have studio access, and the ability to fire at our studio for $495. Also, if you are a community studio and want to purchase access for your studio members, you can do so with the "community studio package" option below. BIPOC folks pay $150 for class with no access or $250 with studio access. Email cor@gasworksnyc.com for a discount code. Note: there is no greenware storage at the studio with studio access. Here's the lineup:

Eva Funderburgh will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration on how she makes her "flyer" sculptures
Natalia Arbalaez will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration on how to make quick gestural figures using the solid method
Michelle Im will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of "faking porcelain-a journey into low-fired ceramics."
Sydnie Jimenez will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of pinching and coiling to build a face and surface decoration with slip.
Jen Allen will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of 3-d sketching and template making for plates, vases, and cups
Shea Burke will give an artist talk followed by a presentation on experimental coil building
Candice Methe will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of how she makes her energy towers and works with terra sigilatta
Lalese Stamps will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of slip-casting tips and tricks
Margaret Kinkeade will give an artist talk followed by a demonstration of handbuilding using tarpaper templates and underglaze inlay

So very excited for @evafunderburgh to join Women + GNC in Clay! Eva will be giving a demonstration on these magical “flyer” sculptures as demonstrated here. We’ve been in love with Eva’s work for a long time and can’t wait to see how these creatures come to life.

If you’ve been looking to get into classes with us this Winter, here’s your way in! We are now offering three price points: zoom only for $295, or take classes, have studio access, and the ability to fire at our studio for $495. Also, if you are a community studio and want to purchase access for your studio members, you can do so with the “community studio package” option. BIPOC folks pay $150 for class with no access or $250 with studio access. 

This series is really special for us and we hope to keep it going. Please share with anyone who you think might be interested! link in bio to register❤️

Making a lot of mess in order to make something look clean.

I’m so thrilled with this piece. It’s waiting for its bisque before the spring Anagama firing. It was very finicky trying to get the iron rich clay to play nicely with the New Zealand porcelain, but I think it was worth the effort. 
.

#ceramics #ceramicsculpture #instaceramics #woodfireceramics #ceramicsofinstagram #sculpture #handmade #womenwhowoodfire #anagama #contemporaryceramics #wufar
A snowy loading day at Santatsugama! We’ve made excellent progress today, stopping with slightly more than half the kiln.  So much hard work from everyone involved!

Santatsugama is off and running! Firing number #67 was lit last night at 7pm. We’ll fire for 100-110 hours. Last I heard the front was at 1400f! This is the snowiest I’ve ever seen it here - it definitely is scuttling my camping plans.

Hour 55 at the anagama! We’re far ahead of schedule. @clayandcoffee and Debrah have been side stoking all night. Cone 8 is already falling in the middle of the kiln, while cone 11 is just soft up front. 
.
#ceramics #ceramicsculpture #instaceramics #woodfireceramics #ceramicsofinstagram #sculpture #handmade #womenwhowoodfire #anagama #contemporaryceramics #wufar

Hour 84, temperature 2190f throughout the kiln. Cone 10 is down in the far back, 11 down in front. The kiln is running like a dream! Looks like we’ll shut it down tonight, 36 hours early. 
.
#ceramics #ceramicsculpture #instaceramics #woodfireceramics #ceramicsofinstagram #sculpture #handmade #womenwhowoodfire #anagama #contemporaryceramics #wufar

And thus we wrap up firing 67 at Santatsugama! We fired for about 87 hours, followed by 4.5 hours of reduction cooling. A few hours after that, we put a few cubic feet of hardwood charcoal into the far back firebox - a fun experience with contact reduction, inspired by @hearth.tea.and.table. I feel really positive about the whole thing, though we’ll have to wait more than a week before we can unload. 
.
 It’s wild to announce this, but this has been my last time managing Ken Lundemo’s kiln here in Seabeck, WA. I love all the folks, and won’t be disappearing. However, I have some pretty exciting plans in the work for this spring. They involve 10 acres of land, a beautiful view, and sketched up design for a pair of train kilns. More details will follow soon!

I took an evening to sort my fliers for my upcoming kiln crowdfunding. It’s happening, I swear! 
  I’m not sure if I’ll have time to launch it in early May after this upcoming wood firing, or if I’ll need to wait until June after the next wood firing! 
  f you want to make sure not to miss it, sign up for my email list in my profile! 
.

This May, I’m going to get a chance to fire with @woodfire at his train kiln in Illinois. I’m so excited for this. Train kilns are fascinating design, but a type of kiln I have very little experience with. It’s also what I’m planning on building. Being able to fire with both @pleasant_hill_pottery and Simon Levin in one month is going to be an amazing introduction, right as I’m planning my own kiln. Doing two wood firings inside of a month is going to be a wild ride, but I can’t wait! Let’s go!
.
#ceramics #keramik #porcelain #ceramicmonsters
Just finished part one of a major sculpting marathon! Fueled with Easter candy and PBS documentaries. Fingers crossed that they all make it through the bisque firing!

We’re about 24 hours into firing the @pleasant_hill_pottery train kiln! This beast fires with such a different rhythm than an anagama kiln. We have to keep it stuffed full of wood at all times to keep the temp from taking off! We’re at about 2000 degrees, with cone 8 down in the front of the kiln. Probably less than a full day left. 
  It’s been a delight firing with Jesse, @annieoclay, @heather.hitt, and @bluewaterpottery

I’m back home from four lovey days at @pleasant_hill_pottery, where I fired his train kiln with @annieoclay, @heather.hitt, @bluewaterpottery, and more. 
  This is a fascinating little kiln, built in the frame of an old gas kiln. We had to keep it absolutely stuffed with wood to keep the temperature from skyrocketing. We used 3 cords in 44 hours! In the end, we finished the firing with waste vegetable oil for a glossy finish. I can’t wait to see the unload. 
.
#ceramics #woodfire #wufar #woodfiredceramics #womenwhowoodfire #trainkiln #woodkiln #woodfiredpotterykilns

TALK and POP-UP SHOW!
I’m so excited to announce that @gasworksnyc will be hosting both @alex.olson.arts and myself on May 20th. We’ll each be giving a talk about our career and experience, and taking questions from the audience. We’ll also both have a small selection of work on display and for sale!

I’m nearly done preparing to fire with @woodfire in Illinois next week! From there, I’ll be traveling on to NYC. On May 20th, I’ll be giving a talk at @gasworksnyc. 
  This has been such a wild marathon, but such a good one. I’ll get back to progress on my own wood kiln in June! 
 .

I’m spending the week in the beautiful prairie of Illinois, wood firing with @woodfire @glan60104 @elinhughesceramics. We’re about 16 hours into a two day firing. It’s been so great to learn so many different firing methods. 

#wufar #woodfire #trainkiln #woodfiredpottery

We wrapped up firing on the 11th! It ended up being a harder firing than expected, most likely due to a tightly stacked kiln at lots of tiny pieces. We went for 53 hours, a more than 4 hours more than normal. I then down fired it for 8 hours to 1710 while  @woodfire, @wu_meng_che_, and @elinhughesceramics got some sleep. 
  It’s been so fascinating talking about the details of firing with Simon. I’ve learned so much for my future train kiln, and for firing the anagama. I can’t wait to see the result when we unload on Sunday. In the meantime, I drove north to visit @amysongceramics, who just happened to be wrapping up firing her train kiln as well!
.
#trainkiln #woodfire #woodfireceramics

The unloading today was excellent, but I’m discovering I hardly took any photos! The flashing on my sculptures was so very lovely and subtle. As soon as I reach New York City, I’ll take some more shots! In the meantime, please enjoy this bowl of beasts.
.
#wufar #trainkiln #simonlevin #woodfiredceramics

I unpacked my bag this morning to take a better look at some of pieces from @woodfire’s firing. The results range from so subtle to extremely flashy! I can’t wait to really digest the results. 
.
The tiny beasts will be part of my kiln crowdfundr, launching sometime next month. The rest will have to wait for a sale later this summer! 
.
Thank you to @godpots for the tiny beast photo from yesterday!

Resetting my studio and my mind after a solid month (or two) of movement. I still have a lot on my plate, but it feels so good to start from a clean work surface.

I'm so excited to have @jrinehartgallery debut my newest large beast at the Seattle Art Fair! I sculpted "Wanderer" last fall, but it spent months waiting for me to create the correct sun. 18k Gold luster turned out to be just the thing to anchor all our planets in their delicate dance. 
 Visit J. Rinehart at booth C09 to see it in person!

The preview for my kiln fundraiser is now up in my profile! It will launch on Saturday, August the 5th, at 10am pacific. 
  I’m so excited to finally bring this project to reality. I’ve been working so hard for months to line up all the parts of this project. Now, I’ll just need your help! This will also be the largest shop launch that I’ve ever done! I can’t wait for next week.

My crowdfundr to build my kiln has launched, and I'm so grateful for all the support already! We've just passed the halfway mark, and beasts are still available. I can't believe everyone's support. Thank you all! ❤️
 The link is in my profile!
This @evafunderburgh tiny beast traveled with us to New Brunswick to attend the @summervilleartfestival and decided to stay and read. #tinybeastmigration

When you spend a decade hanging out in a parkour gym, you end up with some good friends. Friends who like climbing on things, who are good with power tools, and are down to give up part of their weekend to help build a kiln shed (kiln barn? Kiln palace?). 
  Less than one month after getting the lumber delivered, we’re nearly ready for the roof.

We’ve reached the final day of my crowdfundr! I can’t believe it’s been two months already. The shed is up, but still needs the roof (and a dry day to install it). The bricks are arriving, mostly in the back of our truck, 160 at a time. This is all thanks to everyone’s support. 
  I’m going to have a very busy fall, balancing sculpting with brick stacking with splitting wood. One task I’m very much looking forward to it glazing names onto bricks. There’s still time to get your own name on a brick if you want! The link to the crowdfundr is in my profile’s linktree!

Roofing day, part 1! We started out stacking about 1,000 bricks during a (cloudy) solar eclipse, followed by finishing the fascia boards, lower flashing, and framing the chimney. We only got three sheets of roof up before Mother Nature said no, so we’ll be using the classic blue roof until the next clear day. It’s looking so good, though!
The kiln shed is complete! I’m sure additions will come in the future (gutter, solar lights, rolling barn doors, etc), but we finally have a roof! I’m so happy with it. So many thanks to everyone!
Things are going well out at the cloud kiln! I'm onto the second layer of the walls, learning as I go. It's wild how slow the floors went, but that's also nearly 1/5 the bricks of the whole kiln.
